    "Notably, as shown in the heatmap in Figure 3, the differences between the top and bottom rows (reflecting Position0 vs. Position1) are greater than those between the columns (Time0 vs. Time1).",
    "Specifically, the distractor's position has a stronger influence on attack success than the timing of the action, with a 13.2% difference between early (Po-sition0) and late (Position1) placements, compared to only a 4.0% difference between early (Time0) and late (Time1) action timing.",
    "Additionally, unlike other models, Llama-3 achieves its highest success rate with Position0 and Time1.",
    "This suggests that the optimal timing for distractor effectiveness is not absolute across all models and may vary depending on model-specific characteristics, influencing their susceptibility to FITD attacks.",
